text: The Atlantic City Diablos are an American professional soccer team based in Richland, New Jersey, United States. Founded in 2005, the team plays in Women's Premier Soccer League (WPSL), a national amateur league at the fourth tier of the American Soccer Pyramid. The Diablos' home is the St. Augustine College Preparatory School's athletic stadium, located in the Atlantic City suburb of Richland, where they have played since 2007. The team is owned by Team Dynamics LLC, a highly successful organization dedicated to soccer education and player development at all age levels. Team Dynamics LLC also maintains a team in the National Premier Soccer League (NPSL), also called the Atlantic City Diablos.
